                <head>For the Spectator; To the Citizens of Augusta County</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>B. H. Kibler; Spring Hill, Jan. 17, 1857; [] please copy.</trailer>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Mills</ln>
                        <pf>Mrs.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Kibler</ln>
                        <pf>B. H.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Parts illegible. Letter apparently from physician or medical examiner, in
                    reference to an accusation that an autopsy he performed on a "colored girl" was
                    done unprofessionally. He cries slander. Also refers to exhuming and dissecting
                    the body of a "negro man belonging to Mrs. Mills."</summary>
            </div>
